YK[direct]
YT[ko,seki]
YG[advanced]
PC[https://senseis.xmp.net/?DoubleKoSeki]
C[Double Ko Seki — from Sensei's Library.
If Black takes at a (ac) White takes at b (da), and vice versa.
Neither side can continue locally — this is seki.
Calibration fixture: tromp-taylor rules prevent superko interference.]
AB[ca][ea][db][eb][cc][dc][bd][dd][ae][be][ce][de]
AW[ba][fa][ab][bb][cb][fb][bc][ec][fc][ad][ed][ee][af][bf][cf][df][ef]
LB[ac:a][da:b]
;B[ac]C[Black takes the ko at a.]
(;W[da]C[Correct — White takes the other ko. Double ko seki.])
(;W[pass]C[Wrong — White must respond.]))
